Sure, here are some example sentences that use the Serbian word "napali" in different forms and positions:

1. Nisam ni primetio da su me napali komarci. (*napali*, past participle; "I didn't even notice that mosquitoes had attacked me.")
2. Kad su se pojavili novi svjedoci, napali su ga na laži. (*napali*, past tense; "When new witnesses appeared, they attacked him for lying.")
3. Dok je pokušavao da se odbrani, napali su ga sa svih strana. (*napali*, past tense; "While he was trying to defend himself, they attacked him from all sides.")
4. Napali su me da im pomognem oko organizacije zabave. (*napali*, past tense; "They approached me to help them with organizing the party.")
5. Što si napaljen na tu ideju? (*napaljen*, adjective; "Why are you so excited about that idea?")
6. Nikada se ne bih napalio na takvu vrstu rizika. (*napalio*, past tense; "I would never get excited about that kind of risk.")
7. Ako me više ne budeš napadao, možda ću te saslušati. (*napadao*, past tense; "If you stop attacking me, maybe I'll listen to you.")
8. Da bi napao ovaj problem, moraš imati pravi pristup. (*napao*, past tense; "To tackle this problem, you need to have the right approach.")

I hope these examples help!